text: Schoenobius endochralis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by George Hampson in 1919. It is found in Argentina. The wingspan is 36 mm. The forewings are pale rufous. The hindwings are whitish, tinged with rufous. There is a fine brown terminal line.Annals and Magazine of Natural History (9) 3 (17): 451 ==References== Category:Moths described in 1919 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Schoenobius endochralis
